<br>
I also know how to lead a group, I've played every class except beserker and beastlord to at least level 40.  (I get bored easily apparently.)  I also know trust my abilities to fill any role in the group that needs filling, with the exception of healer.  So far, since the LDoN expansion, I've noticed a trend and took it for granted, I had yet to have a horrible pick up group for an adventure.  Notice the key word in the previous sentence.  Yet.<br>
<br>
Last night I lost it.  Completely lost it.  Granted, I am a jaded player, I've played too long to group with idiots and I have no problem telling you that you are an idiot.  I should have known something was wrong when I was asked to join a group and told all I had to do was sing haste and mana.  But I didn't listen to that little voice of experience.  I didn't obey my gut instinct.  Bad Lyrral.  Bad.<br>
<br>
Group consist of 2 warriors, a paly, a druid, a cleric and me the bard.  I've grouped with the cleric before and trust him to keep me alive.  He also trusts me to keep him alive and mez adds as needed.<br>
<br>
So I am talking to the paly and finding out how confident he is with lull pulling.  Says he's ok.  My lull doesn't last as long as his, but when mine resists I don't usually pull the entire room.  But the leader says the paly is pulling.  Fine.  I'll go along with it.  Mind you, I am the one going over group roles and what everyone needs to do.  Druid, snare, and if they resist, let me know, I have my snare up.  Warrior 1, unless I tell you which one to attack, feel free to attack any of the mezzed mobs.  Warrior 2 and paly, follow the MT and don't you dare break one of my mezzes.  First room goes ok.  Second room goes ok, paly has us move up, however, paly doesn't clear out an adjacent room before that.  Mistake #1.  Druid doesn't tell me snare is being resisted.  Mistake #2.  Holy crap there are 5 other mobs in this room now?  No problem, song of twilight, flute, charm, I can do this.  We get one killed and I am trying desperately to lock down the mobs on the druid and cleric.  I am also ML.  Warrior #2 (who is also the group leader) says, &quot;Loot the mob&quot;.  &quot;How?  I a5m busy m5ezzing 5he5re, num5nut.  It5's one5 mo5b.&quot;  Keep in mind there are now about 3 more mobs joining our little party.  Warrior #2 breaks mobs before main tank, and has the gall to tell me to just sing mana and haste.  Cleric dies (Warrior #2, doesn't understand the TAUNT ability much less what MA/MT means exactly).  Druid dies next, and I call it.  &quot;Run, I have them locked down.&quot;  Warrior #2 tells me to loot the  one mob we killed before zoning.  Yeah, right, like I am going to do that.  Paly, warriors 1 and 2 and me make it to zone and get out.  I am singing mana/health song for paly to help heal us up and have started working out how to handle corpse retrieval.  Cleric goes LD.  Start talking to Warrior #1 in tells.  If cleric doesn't come back, we're outta here.  Get to druid's corpse.  She has yet to consent me.  I'm just keeping the mobs who are staring at me lulled and  spamming druid with tells, consent me, consent me....<br>
<br>
Still not consented.  Fine.  Paly comes and rezzes druid.  Cleric logs back in.  Cleric rezzes himself.  Cleric and druid still have rez effects so I am singing mana for them and Warrior #2 says...&quot;go pull.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Go pull?  Don't you dare.  This is how we're gonna do this.  I am pulling from now on.  Warrior #1 will get mob off me.   Druid, snare, and if it resists LET US KNOW.  Warrior #2, deal out the damage, that's all you have to do.  Paly, do you have stun up?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No.&quot;<br>
<br>
I roll my eyes.  &quot;Get it up.  If a mob looks like it's gonna cast or run, stun the bugger.  Lock 'em down.&quot;<br>
<br>
Leader realizes that I have effectively taken over the group.    He's not happy.  He opines with... &quot;Bards should protect the cleric.&quot;<br>
<br>
Bards should protect the cleric?  Excuse me, while I pick my jaw up off the floor.  &quot;How do you propose I do that?  I don't have taunt, I have an AC for shit and oh yeah, HP's that make pure casters chuckle at me.  You obviously have no clue what a bard is capable of.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I do to.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh?  And have you ever played a bard?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Yeah.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;To what?  Level 20?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;No, 25.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Ok, we're either doing this my way or I am out of here.&quot;  Warrior #1 and I have been talking in tells still and she agrees with me.  If I leave she goes.<br>
<br>
&quot;Laters.&quot;  He disbands me.<br>
<br>
Warrior #1 says in say.  &quot;I'm not staying if it's not a full group and I am certainly not staying, if Lyrral leaves.&quot;<br>
<br>
Here's a little public service announcement from the good bards out there (and god knows there are a lot of twinked, PL'd bad bards).  We know our class and know what we are capable of.  Don't presume you know how to play a class just because you have gotten one to level 20 or 25.  Don't presume to tell us what songs to sing.  We actually know what is best for a group from experience, and despite what you might think you know, we actually know more.<br>
<br>
Ok, /rant off... sorry, just still steaming under the collar from the idiot Warrior #2 telling me that it is my job to protect the cleric....<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Lyrral<br>
<br>
(Damn good bard who actually knows her songs...)   <p>Lyrral on EQ<br>
